                            </p>
                            <ul style="margin: 4.9  startarem 0 0 4.9  startarem; color: #C62828;">
                                <li>$300-$500 in spoiled food</li>
                                <li>$800-$1,200 compressor damage</li>
                                <li>$2,000+ for full replacement</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: #E3F2FD; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                            <p style="margin: 0; color: #1565C0;">
                                <strong>💡 Quick Fix:</strong> Check if the back of your fridge feels hot. If yes, unplug it for 
                                5 minutes and clean the coils with a vacuum. This solves 30% of cooling issues.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h4 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Other LG Refrigerator Issues We Fix:</h4>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; color: #666;">
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>Ice Maker Not Working</strong> - Usually a frozen water line (45-min fix)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>Water Dispenser Problems</strong> - Often a clogged filter ($75-150)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>Strange Noises</strong> - Typically fan motor issues (1-hour repair)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0;">
                            <strong>Error Codes (Er IF, Er FF)</strong> - Fan errors we fix same-day
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 4.9  startarem; color: #666;">
                        <strong>Average Repair Cost:</strong> $200-$450 | <strong>Time:</strong> 4.9  startarhours
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <!-- LG Washer Problems -->
                <div class="problem-card" style="background: white; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 15px; box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
                    <h3 style="color: #1A237E; margin-bottom: 4.9  startarem; font-size: 4.9  startarem;">Why Won't My LG Washer Drain Water?</h3>
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 4.9  startarem;">
                        <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                            <strong>Most Common Cause:</strong> Clogged drain pump filter or kinked drain hose. 
                            The OE error code appears when water can't drain within 10 minutes.
                        </p>
                        <div style="background: #E3F2FD; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                            <p style="margin: 0; color: #1565C0;">
                                <strong>💡 Quick Fix:</strong> Open the small door at the bottom front of your washer. 
                                Remove and clean the drain filter. This fixes 40% of drainage issues instantly.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h4 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Other LG Washer Problems We Solve:</h4>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; color: #666;">
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>UE Error (Unbalanced)</strong> - Suspension rod replacement ($150-300)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>Not Spinning</strong> - Usually door latch or control board (1-hour fix)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
                            <strong>LE Motor Error</strong> - Hall sensor issue (90-minute repair)
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding: 4.9  startarem 0;">
                            <strong>Door Won't Lock</strong> - Door latch assembly replacement ($175-250)
                        </li>
                    </ul>
