    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">LG Appliance Repair FAQs</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-grid">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>How much does LG appliance repair cost?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>LG appliance repair costs vary by model and issue. Our diagnostic fee is $4.9  startar(waived with repair). Most LG repairs range from $200-$500 including parts and labor. We provide upfront pricing before any work begins.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>Do you fix LG Linear Compressor issues?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We do NOT service Linear Compressor repairs. For these specialized repairs, we recommend contacting LG directly or seeking a specialist who focuses on compressor work. We handle all other LG appliance repairs including Smart ThinQ issues, error codes, and general malfunctions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>Do you use genuine LG parts?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! We use authentic LG replacement parts whenever possible. Genuine parts ensure proper fit, function, and longevity. They also help maintain any existing warranty. If LG parts aren't immediately available, we can use high-quality OEM alternatives with your approval.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>Can you fix LG Smart ThinQ appliances?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely! Our technicians are trained on LG's Smart ThinQ technology. We can troubleshoot WiFi connectivity issues, app problems, and smart feature malfunctions. We also use Smart Diagnosis when available to quickly identify problems.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>How quickly can you repair my LG appliance?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We offer same-day service for most LG repairs in Toronto and GTA. Our technicians carry common LG parts, allowing many repairs to be completed on the first visit. For less common parts, we can usually get them within 4.9  startarbusiness days.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>What LG error codes can you fix?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We fix all LG error codes including: OE (drain error), UE (unbalanced load), LE (motor error), Er FF/Er IF (fan errors), d80/d90 (vent blockage), and many more. Our technicians have comprehensive training on LG diagnostic codes.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>Is my older LG appliance worth repairing?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>LG appliances are built to last, so repair is often worthwhile if under 10 years old. As a rule, if repair costs less than 50% of replacement, it's worth fixing. We'll give honest advice about whether repair or replacement makes more sense for your situation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>Do you service commercial LG appliances?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>While we primarily focus on residential LG appliances, we do service light commercial units like those in small offices or rental properties. For heavy commercial equipment, we can refer you to our commercial division.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        <span>What areas of Toronto do you service for LG repairs?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We provide LG appliance repair throughout Toronto including Downtown, North York, Scarborough, Etobicoke, and East York. We also service the entire GTA including Mississauga, Brampton, Vaughan, Richmond Hill, and Markham with same-day availability in most areas.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    


